Package: ars
Type: Package
Title: Adaptive Rejection Sampler
Version: 1.0.0
Depends: R, stats
Imports: pracma, dplyr
Author: Dodo Qian, Hatim Ezbakhe, Naomi Wilcox, and Todd Faulkenberry
Maintainer: Todd Faulkenberry <todd_faulkenberry@berkeley.edu>
Description: This package lets you run adaptive rejection sampling on a distribution of your choice. It uses a series of functions to run through the initialization, sampling, and updating steps of ARS. The functions also perform necessary duties of any ARS process, e.g. testing for log-concavity. An informative slide deck on ARS can be found here: http://www2.stat.duke.edu/~cnk/Links/slides.pdf.
